section 4_3_3_1

  |The annually measured {Glossary.*Glacier glacier} terminus fluctuations from about 500 glaciers worldwide reveal a largely homogeneous {Glossary.*Trend trend} of retreat, despite their variability. More regionally focused studies of length change over different time periods justify high confidence about the trend of glacier length variations.


  

